2 Anyone who knows me that I am a fan of Starbucks.  After having been turned on to them about five years ago, I have never looked back.  Every Starbucks that I have gone to has had exceptional customer service.  Except this one.  I usually order one item:  a grande skinny mocha latte, hot.  I have ordered enough at different Starbucks to know when it is made right, and when it's been royally hijacked.  With this Starbucks, it's a 50/50 chance that the drink will be right.  And, frankly, I'm too lazy to bother to complain or have the staff make another one.  My biggest complaint about this location, however, is the staff.  I often would go here to get schoolwork done or to work on projects for my clients, so I could sometimes spend three to four hours inside.  The amount of vulgar language that I heard coming from their mouths as they bantered with each other was astonishing.  And it wasn't as if they were whispering it; they were openly using this language.  I would hear them talk about their romantic lives, sometimes in details.  How these employees remain employed is beyond me.  What I heard is simply deplorable.  I have since moved from that location and go to a different Starbucks 12 miles or so away.  I made it a point to go back to this Starbucks to see if anything had changed in the six months since my last visit--and it hadn't.  Within one hour of sitting inside doing project work, I heard the expletives as they were bantering.  If you have any sense of professionalism about you or are offended by an occasional expletive from the staff, I would steer away from this location.
